[
    {
        "content": "<p>In roc-pg, <code>Pg.Client</code> has this type: </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Python\"><pre><span></span><code>    <span class=\"n\">Client</span> <span class=\"p\">::</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">stream</span> <span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">TcpStream</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">backend_key</span> <span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Try</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ProtocolBackend</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">KeyData</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Pending</span><span class=\"p\">]),</span>\n    <span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>In the old implementation, <code>TcpStream</code> was just <code>Tcp.Stream</code> imported from the platform (not sure how that worked). <br>\nI was hoping I could just define <code>TcpStream</code> to be some type which has the methods <code>write!</code>, <code>read!</code>, etc. but I can't use a where clause on a type definition so I'm not sure how to do this, or whether it's possible.</p>",
        "id": 609726506,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryce Miller",
        "timestamp": 1783894718
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Would the current idiomatic way to handle this be to have <code>Pg.Client.connect!</code>, et. al just accept a <code>tcp_stream_write</code> function?</p>",
        "id": 609726614,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryce Miller",
        "timestamp": 1783894832
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or should the type become something like this? </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Python\"><pre><span></span><code>    <span class=\"n\">Client</span> <span class=\"p\">::</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">backend_key</span> <span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Try</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ProtocolBackend</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">KeyData</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Pending</span><span class=\"p\">]),</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">stream_read</span><span class=\"err\">!</span> <span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span> <span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">stream_write</span><span class=\"err\">!</span> <span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span> <span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 609726755,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryce Miller",
        "timestamp": 1783895004
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So I did find this: <a class=\"message-link\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/231634-beginners/topic/library.20depending.20on.20platform.20types/near/606727775\">#beginners &gt; library depending on platform types @ 💬</a>  </p>\n<p>Looks like this is type checking: </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Python\"><pre><span></span><code>    <span class=\"n\">Client</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">stream</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"p\">::</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">backend_key</span> <span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Try</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ProtocolBackend</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">KeyData</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Pending</span><span class=\"p\">]),</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">stream</span> <span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">stream</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">connect</span><span class=\"err\">!</span> <span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n            <span class=\"n\">host</span> <span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Str</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n            <span class=\"n\">port</span> <span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">U16</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n            <span class=\"n\">user</span> <span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Str</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n            <span class=\"n\">auth</span> <span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kc\">None</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">Password</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Str</span><span class=\"p\">)],</span>\n            <span class=\"n\">database</span> <span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Str</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n            <span class=\"n\">tcp_connect</span><span class=\"err\">!</span> <span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Str</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">U16</span> <span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">Try</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">stream</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">),</span>\n        <span class=\"p\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">Try</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Client</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n            <span class=\"n\">where</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">stream</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">write</span><span class=\"err\">!</span> <span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">stream</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">U8</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">Try</span><span class=\"p\">({},</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">)]</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">connect</span><span class=\"err\">!</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"p\">{</span> <span class=\"n\">host</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">port</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">user</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">auth</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">database</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">tcp_connect</span><span class=\"err\">!</span> <span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n            <span class=\"n\">stream</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">tcp_connect</span><span class=\"err\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">host</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">port</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"err\">?</span>\n            <span class=\"n\">stream</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">write</span><span class=\"err\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ProtocolFrontend</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">startup</span><span class=\"p\">({</span> <span class=\"n\">user</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">database</span> <span class=\"p\">}))</span><span class=\"err\">?</span>\n            <span class=\"n\">crash</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"todo\"</span>\n        <span class=\"p\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 609737529,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryce Miller",
        "timestamp": 1783903945
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It looks like I have to repeat the <code>where [stream.write! : stream, List(U8) -&gt; Try({}, _)]</code> for every function that needs to write to a TCP stream. </p>\n<p>Am I missing a better way to do this?</p>",
        "id": 609815293,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryce Miller",
        "timestamp": 1783941756
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>My concern here is that I when I have a constraint like the one on <code>stream.write!</code> above, I want to use the same constraint for all functions. I don't want to accidentally have one helper with a different type signature on the constraint. </p>\n<p>I tried this, but it doesn't seem to work: </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Python\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">send_with_sync</span><span class=\"err\">!</span> <span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">tcp_stream</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">U8</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">Try</span><span class=\"p\">({},</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">where</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">tcp_stream</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">write</span><span class=\"err\">!</span> <span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">TcpWrite</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">tcp_stream</span><span class=\"p\">)]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">send_with_sync</span><span class=\"err\">!</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">stream</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nb\">bytes</span><span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">content</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">Bytes</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Encode</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sequence</span><span class=\"p\">([</span><span class=\"nb\">bytes</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">ProtocolFrontend</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sync</span><span class=\"p\">])</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">stream</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">write</span><span class=\"err\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">content</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">TcpWrite</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">stream</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">stream</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">U8</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">Try</span><span class=\"p\">({},</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">SomeErr</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Str</span><span class=\"p\">)])</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 609833388,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryce Miller",
        "timestamp": 1783947834
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>Am I missing a better way to do this?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I think there is no better way and I suspect it is a deliberate choice <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"281383\">@Richard Feldman</span></p>",
        "id": 609844318,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1783950770
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>we've talked about having aliases for this, e.g. so you could do <code>where [tcp_stream.Write]</code> (and then we could have a similar thing for <code>.Eq</code> and whatnot) but haven't implemented it yet</p>",
        "id": 609845120,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1783950953
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I wanted to try to see how it felt to do without it before adding it...I think for now it's best to try it as-is and then see how much of a pain point it is in practice after there are actual users of the package, and then we can reevaluate based on how things go in practice!</p>",
        "id": 609845396,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1783951026
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ok fair enough, I can appreciate that approach!</p>",
        "id": 609846500,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryce Miller",
        "timestamp": 1783951268
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also, perhaps I should have spent more time digging through Zulip before asking this question. If so, I apologize. I did finally find the messages that explained the rationale behind disallowing where clauses for type declarations, it just took a bit of digging <span aria-label=\"sweat smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f605\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat smile\">:sweat_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 609847035,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryce Miller",
        "timestamp": 1783951404
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>All good :)</p>",
        "id": 609847149,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1783951438
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The <a href=\"https://github.com/roc-lang/zulip-export\">zulip-export repo</a> can also be useful to automate the search with an LLM.</p>",
        "id": 609847354,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1783951488
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah it's all good, thanks for posting about it! <span aria-label=\"smiley\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f603\" role=\"img\" title=\"smiley\">:smiley:</span></p>",
        "id": 609847528,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1783951529
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do you think it might be worth adding something to the error message for where clauses on type declarations that suggests what to do instead? (put the where clauses on function annotations)</p>",
        "id": 609848244,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryce Miller",
        "timestamp": 1783951695
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah, I like that idea! Want to open an issue for it?</p>",
        "id": 609848391,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1783951730
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sure!</p>",
        "id": 609848467,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryce Miller",
        "timestamp": 1783951749
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"522634\">Bryce Miller</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/231634-beginners/topic/How.20to.20define.20an.20interface.3F/near/609847035\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Also, perhaps I should have spent more time digging through Zulip before asking this question. If so, I apologize. I did finally find the messages that explained the rationale behind disallowing where clauses for type declarations, it just took a bit of digging <span aria-label=\"sweat smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f605\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat smile\">:sweat_smile:</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>if you still have the tab or thread name, can you link it here too? to make it a bit easier for someone searching for this same thing in the future <span aria-label=\"smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"smile\">:smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 609940818,
        "sender_full_name": "Jared Ramirez",
        "timestamp": 1783967021
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here's what I found, though this references outdated syntax: <a class=\"message-link\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/304641-ideas/topic/where.20clause.20changes/near/528185795\">#ideas &gt; where clause changes @ 💬</a></p>",
        "id": 609945332,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryce Miller",
        "timestamp": 1783968565
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also in that where-clause thread - is the <code>.module</code> lookup syntax on pause? Concretely, I have wanted to be able to generically use the <code>default</code> function of numbers, or the <code>highest</code> and <code>lowest</code> associated with their modules.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code># Ofc, you could just have an extra argument for the fill value\nMyContainer.fill(n) : () -&gt; MyContainer(t) where [t.module.default : () -&gt; t]\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The other one I had in mind was generic conversions</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>A.to_b : A -&gt; B\nB.from : x -&gt; B where [x.to_b : x -&gt; B]\nconv : g -&gt; h where [h.module.from : g -&gt; h]\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>which may not be something you want to allow anyhow <span aria-label=\"sweat smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f605\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat smile\">:sweat_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 610070361,
        "sender_full_name": "Jonathan",
        "timestamp": 1784026832
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I am guessing we just forgot about it :p <br>\nDo we still want to add <code>x.module.mod_function</code> support inside <code>where</code> <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"281383\">@Richard Feldman</span>?</p>",
        "id": 610783556,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1784116028
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>oh we just ended up going with the syntax where we skip the <code>.module</code> part <span aria-label=\"smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"smile\">:smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 610802020,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1784120846
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so the type signature in that example would be: </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>conv : g -&gt; h where [h.from : g -&gt; h]\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 610802182,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1784120890
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>How do you call <code>from</code> though in the body of the function?</p>",
        "id": 610802410,
        "sender_full_name": "Jonathan",
        "timestamp": 1784120946
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>conv : g -&gt; h where [h.from : g -&gt; h]\nconv = |arg| {\n    H : h\n\n    H.from(arg)\n}\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 610803301,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1784121183
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>H : h</code> creates a type alias of the <code>h</code> type variable that's in scope from the annotation</p>",
        "id": 610803451,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1784121227
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ooooooh, that's nifty. Thanks <span aria-label=\"thumbs up\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f44d\" role=\"img\" title=\"thumbs up\">:thumbs_up:</span></p>",
        "id": 610803497,
        "sender_full_name": "Jonathan",
        "timestamp": 1784121239
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>at which point you can call <code>H.from</code> normally</p>",
        "id": 610803508,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1784121242
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>sure! <span aria-label=\"smiley\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f603\" role=\"img\" title=\"smiley\">:smiley:</span></p>",
        "id": 610803527,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1784121247
    }
]